cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on linear support vector machine classifiers, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves image classification, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and game theory suggests a possible fit with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
